Minor comment:

{code}
+    String defaultVal = null;
+    String val = HiveConf.getVar(conf, ConfVars.LLAP_IO_ENABLED, defaultVal);
+    boolean isEnabled = (val != null) ? Boolean.parseBoolean(val) : LlapProxy.isDaemon();
{code}

You could just use the HiveConf.getBoolVar() method with a default LlapProxy.isDaemon() to get the same effect.

Just for clarification, user could set this configuration to false and the daemon would not use the IOElevator? Is that the right way to look at this configuration or did you want the daemon to always use IOElevator?
